    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  males or females over the age of 50 with early-stage dementia as described by Global
             Deterioration Scale levels 2,3,4 or 5.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  subjects who have a medical condition that significantly predispose them to falls
             (Meneire's disease or Parkinson's disease)

          -  subjects without a caregiver/spouse to assist with the completion of a Fall Diary

          -  subjects unable to stand independently or safely walk a short distance either unaided
             or with the support of an assistive device

          -  subjects unable to safely complete the balance and gait evaluations.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
